PETITION

The petition command allows you to seek the assistance from any available
staff member online.  The syntax is as follows:  petition <question to ask>.

You may only petition once every 5 minutes to prevent insistent players from
spamming our staff with petitions.

You are not to use the petition system to report bugs, typos or to make
suggestions or simply because you want to chat.  If you are looking for
a specific staff member for some reason, please use the mail command
instead of the petition command.  They will receive a notification as
soon as the mail is sent if they are online, and if not, they will
receive it as soon as they log on.

If you do have a bug or typo to report, or you want to make a suggestion,
please do so on our forums at http://www.ageofdragons.com/

Before submitting a petition you must first do everything possible to
solve your problem on your own.  That includes using help files (if
there is one and it is up-to-date), checking the online forums, and
asking other players using the newbie and chat commands.  If, and only
if, your situation cannot be resolved using those methods, then you
may submit a petition.

In the case of problems with another player, such as harrassment, cheating,
or some other serious problem, in this case do not seek help from other
players, but instead submit a petition right away, even if you or others
think the matter to be trivial.  We take harrassment, bullying, cheating,
and other out-of-character mistreatment very seriously here, as we pride
ourselves on having a friendly, positive, drama-free atmosphere on our
MUD.

If you do not get a response from petition our GMs, please send a mail
using the mail command to the staff member in charge of the area you
are having an issue with.  These people are as follows:
Dran: All mob, object, room or zone issues.  Bugs should be posted on the forum.
      However, at times you may need special attention, such as when your
      character stats are messed up or something.  In this case please
      contact Dran if your petition is unanswered.
Gicker: Administrative and Code Issues.  See above with respect to bugs.

