CHALLENGE FEAT-COMBAT-CHALLENGE FEAT-IMPROVED-COMBAT-CHALLENGE FEAT-GREATE

The combat challenge series of feats is used for tanking mobs.  It is done
through the @Ychallenge@n command, and will cause any targeted mobs who are
not currently fighting someone else who is not partied with you, to attack you.

You may either specify a specific mob to challenge, or you may specify 'all'
and have all mobs in the room who are not otherwise occupied attack you.
The 'all' effect requires the improved version of this feat.

These actions use up combat actions to perform.  See the following table:

Highest Feat Possessed | One Mob       | All Mobs
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Combat Challenge       | Stanard       | Impossible
Improved               | Move          | Standard
Greater                | Minor         | Move
Epic                   | Minor         | Minor

Each feat has a prerequisite.  See the following table:

Feat             | Prerequisites
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Combat Challenge | diplomacy skill 5 ranks
Improved         | combat challenge, diplomacy skill 10 ranks
Greater          | improved combat challenge, diplomacy skill 15 ranks
Epic             | greater combat challenge, diplomacy skill 20 ranks

You will receive a bonus to any attempted challenge if you are a
smaller size than your opponent.
