HOW-TO-PLAY

A MUD is a text game and is run through typing commands into your input bar (if
you're using a MUD client that is.  If you don't have one consider using
MUSHClient: http://www.gammon.com.au/mushclient/mushclient.htm).  Everything
that is done on this game is done by typing in a text command, and every output
is also received in text displayed to your screen.

So playing this game comes down to typing commands and responding to output
from the game.

Some of the important commands you will need right away are:
who - displays a list of who is online (if you haven't met the person it 
    might display a description instead of a name)
say - allows you to speak with people in the same room
chat (d20 only) - allows you to speak with everyone on the game
rsay (d20 only) - allows you to speak with other people in the room 'in character'
    (role playing). Awards experience and rp points.
tell - allows you to send a private message to another person in the game
north/east/south/west/ne/se/sw/ne/up/down - allows you to move from one room to the 
    next.
look - allows you to see what is in the room, or if targetting on a mob, player or 
    object, will display information about that entity
score - allows you to see basic information about your own character
hit/attack - allows you to attack monsters or players
cast - allows you to cast spells if you are a spellcaster (type help cast if you are 
    on d20 mud as there are different cast commands for each class)
memorize - allows you to memorize spells if you are a spellcaster class (on d20 
    version you should type help memorize)
help - displays a menu with information about how to play the game
help - displays information about the topic specified (help newbie is a good place 
    to start)
flee - allows you to escape combat if things go poorly
recall (d20 only) allows you to go back to the start room if you get lost

See Also: @YCOMMAND SUMMARY@n, @YNEWBIE@n
