CRAFTING CUSTOM-CRAFTING

The crafting system on d20MUD is designed to allow people to both supplement
their own equipment as an adventurer, or to simply be a full time crafter and
provide crafted goods to other classes in exchange for coin or other items.

The crafting system is comprised of multiple parts:
1. Harvesting materials to use in creation of the item
2. Finding magical essences to imbue the item with magic
3. Finding crystals to direct the power of the magical essence into a specific bonus.
4. Buying a mold to use as the basis for the item desired to be created.

Please read the following help files to learn more about those items:
@YESSENCES@n, @YCRYSTALS@n, @YMOLDS@n, @YMATERIALS@n, @YHARVESTING@n

Once you have collected everything that you need to create the item, find yourself
a crafting station (In Palanthas, they are located in the basement of the Inn of
the Platinum Dragon, just east of the center square), and put all of your materials,
the mold, the crystal, and making sure to put the essence as the last item, all into
the station with the @Yput@n command.

Once you have all of the materials in the station, you need to use the @Ycreate@n
command to create your item.  There are a number of pre-requisites that need to
be met in order to create the item, but the basic syntax of the command is,
'create <description of the item to be created>'

The description can be anything you want, but it MUST be role play oriented, and
it must coincide with a medieval theme.  If it does not, the item may be taken from
you without reimbursement.  The description must also contain the name of the item
type, determined by the mould (some item types have multiple possibilities) and the
name of the material being used.  You may use color in your description as well if
you like, though please be tasteful.

Once you type the create command, if all of the requisites are met, the crafting
process will begin, and a certain amount of time later, depending on the type of
item being created, you will be rewarded with the item you wanted to make and
a certain amount of artisan experience as well.

See Also: @YSYNTHESIZE@n, @YDISENCHANT@n, @YHARVESTING@n, @YGEMSTONES@n, @YRESIZE@n, @YRESTRING@n, @YCONVERT@n
@YSUPPLY ORDERS@n
