ESSENCES MAGICAL-ESSENCES CRAFTING-ESSENCES DIVIDE

Magical essences are small globes of glass or crystal filled with the very
essence of magic itself.  They are created by a powerful ritual meant to harness
the surrounding magical energy, or simply by extracting magical power from an
existing magical item.

Magical essences come in a number of varieties, but the most common is the power
essence.  This type of essence is used to fuel crafters in their desire to create
magical items.

A power essence can be of minor, lesser, medium, greater or major power.  The
higher up in that list, the greater the magical bonus will be on the item,
determined by the crystal used in the crafting process.

Essences of the same type and power grade can be combined in the crafting process
to increase the base bonus.  For every 4 essences of the same type and power grade
put into a crafting station, the base bonus of the essence will be increased by
1x.  So 4 minor essences used on a damage crystal, will result in +2 damage instead
of +1.  8 will be +3 instead of +1.  Used with a max hit point crystal, it will
be +10 to max hp instead of +5 for 4 essences, or +15 for 8 essences.  Please note
that the max bonus of the item, is still capped by the level of the crystal.  This
means that if the bonus determined by the essences creates an item with a minimum
usable level greater than the level of the crystal, the bonus will be shifted down
until it is within the level of the crystal, or the minimum bonus amount for that
bonus type, whichever is greater.

Major, greater, medium, and lesser essence can be divided into multiple minor
essences by using the @Ydivide@n command on them.
Dividing a major essence produces 5 minors.
Dividing a greater essence produces 4 minors.
Dividing a medium essence produces 3 minors.
Dividing a lesser essence produces 2 minors.

See Also: @YCRYSTALS@n, @YDISENCHANT@n, @YCRAFTING@n
#0
CRYSTALS MAGICAL-CRYSTALS CRAFTING-CRYSTALS

Crystals are pieces of glass, crystal or gemstone that have been infused with alchemical
properties, which can be used in combination with magical essences to provide a certain
type of bonus to crafted equipment.

Each crystal has both an apply type and a level.  The level is the maximum level that
the item being created can be, and the apply type is the type of bonus that will be
applied to the item being crafted.  Please note that only one crystal may be used
per crafting session, and any additional ones added will be wasted.

If the bonus provided by magical essences is higher than the level of the crystal,
the item will be downgraded until it is within the level of the crystal, or until
it has the minimum bonus amount for that type, whichever is greater.

Harvested gem stones can be synthesized into crystals to be used for crafting
with the @Ysynthesize@n command and the alchemy skill.

See Also: @YGEMSTONES@n, @YSYNTHESIZE@n, @YCRAFTING@n
