MOLDS CRAFTING-MOLDS

Crafting molds are really just existing, mundane items, that have been made
to specification by authoritative crafters.  They can most often be found
as the stock items sold in the marketplaces of various cities around the world.

The crafting mold determines the type of item that will be created in the
crafting process, as well as how many materials are needed.

See Also: @YMATERIALS@n, @YCRAFTING@n, @YHARVESTING@n
#0
MATERIALS CRAFTING-MATERIALS

Crafting materials are harvested natural resources that can be used in the
creation of custom equipment through the crafting system.

Every different type of item will require a different kind of material, with
most items having several options as to what you can use, as well as different
amounts of materials depending on how large and dense the item is.

The various kinds of materials are:

Hard Metals: Steel/Iron, Cold Iron, Mithril, Adamantine
Soft Metals: Copper, Silver, Gold, Platinum
Leather: Low Quality Hides, Medium Quality Hides, High Quality Hides, Dragonhide
Wood: Alderwood, Yew, Oak, Darkwood
Cloths: Hemp, Wool, Cotton, Velvet, Satin, Silk
Gemstones: Obisidian, Onyx, Ruby, Sapphire, Emerald, Diamond

The better the material is (the further to the right in the lists above), the more
artisan experience it will award for a successful harvest or crafting session.

See Also: @YHARVESTING@n, @YCRAFTING@n

