DISENCHANTING

The disenchanting process allows an alchemist to use various processes to extract
the magical power from an existing magical item and store it in a magical essence.

The ability is based on the artisan's alchemy skill, for which higher skills allow
for the disenchanting of more powerful items.

The process is done by using the @Ydisenchant@n command.

See Also: @YESSENCES@n
#0
HARVESTING

Harvesting is the process of going out into the wilds and using your various
skills to extract natural resources from your environment.

Harvesting is broken up into four main types:

@Ymine@n   - Mining    : hard and soft metals and gemstones (hills, mountains or caves)
@Yfarm@n   - Farming   : cloths and food ingredients (fields)
@Yhunt@n   - Hunting   : leathers and food ingredients (fields, hills, mountains, forests)
@Yforest@n - Foresting : wood (forests)

Using one of the harvesting commands above will give you a chance to find a random
material of the type associated with the type of place you are in.  The greater your
skill in that area of harvesting, the better the chance of both finding something, and
finding something good.

@YNOTE@n: The new command for all harvesting node types is '@Yharvest@n'.

See Also: @YMATERIALS@n, @YCRAFTING@n, @YGEMSTONES@n, @YESSENCES@n, @YCRYSTALS@n
