FEAT FEATS

In the d20 System, a feat is one type of ability a character may gain through level
progression. Feats are different from skills in that characters can vary in competency
with skills, while feats typically provide set bonuses to or new ways to use existing
abilities. Many feats have prerequisite levels, base attack bonuses, or other skills, 
feats or abilities which must be obtained before they can be acquired.

You may gain help on a specific feat by typing help feat <name>.

You can list your feats that you know by typing @Yfeats@n.

You can list the feats that are available to you to choose by typing @Yfeats available@n.
You can list feat descriptions by typing @Yfeats available descs@n or feat prerequisites
by typing @Yfeats avail requisistes@n and finally you can list any classfeats
of your currently active class by typing @Yfeats available classfeats@n.

You can list all feats in the game by typing @Yfeats complete@n.
@n
For more info on a specific feat, type @Yhelp feat <feat name>@n.
For example, @Yhelp feat track@n.

Feats are learned during the levelling process by using the @Ylevelup@n command
when you have enough experience to gain a new level.

Everyone gains 1 feat at level 1, plus 1 feat for every level they gain that
is odd in number.  Some classes gain additional class feats selectable from a
specific list at various level intervals as well.

