SKILL-BLUFF TAUNT FEINT

Bluff (Cha)
Check

Bluff can be used in role play situations to try and convince someone of 
something.  It is opposed by a character's lore skill.

You can use the Bluff skill to help you hide. A successful Bluff check 
gives you the momentary diversion you need to attempt a Hide check while 
people are aware of you.

Combat

In combat, you can use the @Yfeint@n and @Ytaunt@n commands to lower your
opponent's AC. These tactics both use your bluff skill and the effects
stack with each other (but note that repeated attempts do not stack).
Feinting is a standard action and taunting is a minor action.  If
successful, the effects last for 1+CHA modifier rounds.
Feinting removes your opponent's DEX bonus to AC, while taunting
removes 2 deflection bonus from your opponent.

Special

A ranger gains a bonus on Bluff checks when using this skill against a 
favored enemy.

If you have the Persuasive feat, you get a +2 bonus on Bluff checks.
Synergy

If you have 5 or more ranks in Bluff, you get a +2 bonus on Diplomacy, 
Intimidate, and Sleight of Hand checks, as well as on Disguise checks made 
when you know you're being observed and you try to act in character. 
