#0
PVP MURDER

Player vs player combat is available on an opt-in basis, and there are rules
in place to help keep it fair and enjoyable.  By default, a character is
protected from pvp combat and can neither attack nor be attacked.
Players can toggle their participation in pvp combat using the @Ypvp@n command.
Any character who has chosen to enable pvp will have a (@GPvP@n) flag shown
beside their name in the WHO list.  This flag will also appear beside their
description.  You can only initiate pvp combat against a player of
greater or equal level to your own (or to your mentor level if you have
mentor enabled).  Combat is initiated by typing @Ymurder@n <victim>.
This begins a 30-minute timer for both players during which period neither
player can disable their pvp flag.  So beware that when you engage in
pvp combat, you open yourself to further attacks and/or retaliation.
Note also that experience is neither gained nor lost by either party
regardless of the outcome.

Please remember to adhere to mud policies when engaging in pvp combat.
The pvp system is for role playing purposes - this is not a pk mud.
Harassment or abuse of the pvp system will result in revokation of a
player's pvp ability.

See Also: @YRULES EVIL@n, @YRULES RESPECT@n, @YMENTOR@n
