CLASS-CLERIC
@n The cleric is the ultimate divine spellcaster, and testament to the power of
 the pantheon. Wielding spells and abilities gifted to them by their gods, the
 cleric can serve as anything from a goodly healer to an agent of destruction.
 Unlike many other spellcasters, he can wear heavy armor without casting penalty
 although he still must train to use martial weapons.

 Like the gods they serve, clerics can be of any alignment. Typically, clerics
 are the same alignment as their deity, although some are one step away from
 their respective deities alignment.

@YCleric Class Features@n
 Alignment:    Any (Same as deity, or one step removed)
 Hit Die:      d8
 Primary Stat: Wisdom

@YSpells@n
 A cleric casts divine spells, which are drawn from the cleric spell list. However,
 his alignment may restrict him from casting certain spells opposed to his moral or
 ethical beliefs.

 A cleric must choose and prepare his spells in advance using the @Ymem@n command.
 Ex: mem bless
     mem cure-light-wounds

 A cleric casts spells using the @Ypray@n command.
 Ex: pray <spell> <target>

 To prepare or cast a spell, a cleric must have a Wisdom score equal to at least
 10 + the spell level. The Difficulty Class for a saving throw against a clerics
 spell is 10 + the spell level + the clerics Wisdom modifier. 

@YClass Skills@n
 Combat Tactics (Dex), Concentration (Con), Craft (Int), Diplomacy (Cha),
 Handle Animal (Cha), Heal (Wis), Lore (Int), Spellcraft (Int).

@YDomain Class Skills@n
 A cleric who chooses the Travel domain adds Survival (Wis) to their class
 skill list. A cleric who chooses Trickery adds Bluff (Cha), Disguise (Cha),
 and Hide (Dex) to their class skill list.

@YDomains@n
 A cleric, after choosing their deity, selects two domains from that deity's
 portfolio. These domains grant the cleric access to specific domain spells
 as well as potential extra abilties. Type help domains for a listing of
 domains, and help domain <name> for a specific domain listing.

 Skill Points at 1st Level: (2 + Int modifier) x 4
 Skill Points at Each Level:  2 + Int modifier

@YWeapon and Armor Proficiency@n
 All simple weapons, with all types of armor (light, medium, heavy), and
 with shields (except tower shields). Each deity has a favored weapon, and
 his or her clerics consider it a point of pride to wield that weapon. A
 cleric who chooses the War domain receives the Weapon Focus feat related to
 that weapon as a bonus feat. He also receives the appropriate Martial Weapon
 Proficiency feat as a bonus feat, if the weapon falls into that category.

For a table explaining Cleric level gains, type @Yhelp table cleric@n.
For a spell table for Clerics, type @Yhelp spelltable cleric@n.
For a spell listing for Clerics, type @Yhelp spelllist cleric@n.
To cast a cleric spell, type @Ypray@n.
