4 COMMUNICATION
@nThere are quite a few forms of communcating with other players in the game.
These forms can be broken into two seperate sections, OOC and IC, or rather,
out of character and "in character".
@n
The first form we're going to go over is out of character communication.
This is the type of communication to use when trying to converse as a player
as opposed to as a roleplayed character. To say something out of character to
everyone in your current room, simply type "ooc" followed by what you would
like to say. For example: ooc how do I set my recall point to here?
@n
You can also communication OOC globally to everyone in the game via the "chat"
channel. Simply type "chat" followed by what you would like to say.
For example: chat How do I join a quest?
@n
If you are in a group of adventurers, you may want to specifically talk to
just members of your group. To do this, type "gt" for grouptalk, followed
by what you'd like to say.
@n
Finally, there is a direct means of communication between players known as
tells To use a tell, type "tell" followed by the persons name, followed
then by your message. For example: tell mask Stop playing tricks on meeee!
@n
There is also in character communcation. Think of these following forms of
communication as a way to roleplay your character. Roleplay can be reviewed
by the administration of the game and rewarded for quality.
@n
To say something in character to everyone in the room, type "say" followed by
what you would like to say.
@n
To shout something to everyone within an area, type "shout" followed by what
you'd like to shout about.
@n
To bellow something at a great distance to everyone in the game, you need to
holler as hard as you can. Type "holler" followed by your epic message which
will ring from the mountains to the valleys below.
@n
There are also "socials". Socials are fun built in expressions and actions
that can be used alone, or targetting another player. For a list for socials,
type "socials" by itself. To enact a social, simply type the social name,
followed optionally by a target.
For example: @Cscratch self@n
For example: @Cwink Ilmater@n
