NEWBIE-GUIDE NEW-PLAYER-GUIDE GUIDE

Welcome to the game.  As you will come to see, if you haven't already,
this game comes with something of a learning curve, especially if you
are new to d20 rules.  If that is the case type @YHELP D20@n.

Currently, the only starting city is Palanthas, which is the home
of the Knights of Solamnia and Forces of Whitestone.  Once you finish
character generation you will find yourself at a fountain with a
mysterious old lady and perhaps a few players there.  If you do see
any players there, try to strike up a conversation with them, using
the ooc or rsay commands.  The latter is an in character, role play
say command, which will allow you to earn experience and other bonuses
simply by talking to other people while pretending to be the character
you're playing.

You'll notice that the mysterious old lady mob is a quest giver.  The
first thing you want to do when you're ready to kill things is type
'quest join 1'.  This will join the first quest.  Then go east 5 times
and north once, then up.  Once here in the Gardens of the Blue Phoenix
kill sparrows until you finish the quest.

Combat is turn based, with autoattack turned on by default.  There are
still a few glitches in the combat system, so bear with us if you notice
something wierd happen, we are working on it.  Remember that in d20 rules
you get a standard, move and minor action to do each round.  Different
things use different types of actions, but in order to get more than one
attack per round you generally need to attack first, and do your other
actions afterwards.

A few things you can try between rounds that only use minor or move 
actions are kick, trip, intimidate, challenge and taunt.  Some of those
are debuffs, and kick does extra damage while trip will cause them to
fall losing ac and giving you an attack of opportunity when they stand
back up.

Once you finish the sparrow quest, go back to the fountain and type
quest join 2.  This time you'll be killing squirrels in the gardens.
After this quest you should have enough experience to gain a level.
Do so by using the levelup command and following the on-screen prompts.

At this point you are level 2.  You have a few options from here.  You
can do bounties at Shandra in the the Inn of the Platinum Dragon between
the gardens and the fountain on the north side of the street.  Type 
'bounty new' to get a random bounty for your general level range, or,
as most people prefer, specify the mob you want to kill.  Be as specific
as possible with your keywords.  For example 'bounty new floppy,white,rabbit'
will give you a bounty to kill rabbits in the gardens, which you can also
team up with the repeatable quest at the fountain for double rewards.  Please
note that you separate keywords with commas for the bounty command (and other
areas of the game) and that you may also need to preceed the keywords with
2. 3. 4. 10. and so forth depending on how many different types of mobs
share those key words.

You can also continue the quest line, though you will need to level up
some by doing bounties, repeatable quests, or just killing things for some
of the quests.  To take this route do the rabbit quest and then go back to
the fountain and type quest join 4.  Keep following the quest line.  Currently
it will take you up to around level 8, and a couple of times during that
journey you will likely need the aid of others to defeat bosses.

Another option is to explore the world.  There are very few areas of the world
right now that are dangerous for newbies to explore.  And the good thing is
you gain experience just by going to places you've never been before.

You can also find some players and role play.  When you use the rsay, emote,
shout or rgsay channels, you get experience and other rewards just for role
playing.

Finally you can try your hand at crafting.  For this we recommend you read
the HELP CRAFING help file and all files referred within it.  Supply orders
are the best place to start with crafting.

Once you get up to level 3 or so, you can start using magical gear.  We've
created an emporium south and west of the fountain using the emporium command
to list and purchase magical gear using quest points you've accumulated doing
quests and bounties.  We recommend you get yourself some magic weapons, armor,
and a few trinkets with natural and delfection ac.  The higher your ac and the
better your weapons, the faster you'll be able to level.  Please note that
stat wise, for all ac types, ac bonuses are multipled by 10.  So for a suit of
+1 armor D&D rules wise, you actually want a suit of +10 armor.

You'll also find some magic gear during your travels, as well as crystals and
power essences.  The latter two are used in custom crafting, through which
you will be able to make gear with your own descriptions.  You can even restring
gear you find to have better descriptions more in line with your character
concept if you like.

That should be enough to get you started on yor journey.  Though I would like to
give a short list of commands that you might find useful:

automap - turns on an ascii map of the surrounding area
camp - uses survival skill to set up a campfire that will improve regen rates
callmount - calls a mount you've purchased (see the vendor at the south gate)
mount - allows you to mount your mount, animal companion or summoned creature
backup - creats a backup of your rent file in case we need to reimburse you.
chat - global channel used for asking questions or general ooc talk
newbie - global channel specific for new players and their questions
spon - toggles spontaneous casting for clerics and druids to cast heals/summons
innate - allows you to use any innate abilities tied to your class/race
random - for making random dice rolls for ooc, skill use or rp purposes
mentor - allows you to reduce your effective level for grouping with lower level
         characters

If at any time you have a question feel free to ask.  We are a friendly group.
Also feel free to use the petition system (HELP PETITION) if you ever need
any help whatsoever from a staff member, though often we respond to chat and
newbie as well.

Enjoy the MUD!

Gicker & the d20MUD Team

