D20-SYSTEM

The d20 System is a game system where almost all rolls are done using a 20-sided
die.

Generally the system works in one of two ways:
- You roll a d20, add your skill/attack bonus/ability score bonus
--- You compare it against a set difficulty class (or dc)
--- You compare it against an opposed roll by the opposing player/mob

When the dice roll is equal to or higher than the dc or opposing roll, you succeed
at the task, otherwise you fail.

Character building is an important part of the d20 system.  Often experienced
players will plan out their entire build at level 1, or at least have a very
good idea of it.  Fortunately we have added a respec command that allows you
to rebuild your character from level 1 for account experience which is easily
gained through role play or mentoring.

We encourage you to test out a number of builds before you settle on one that
fits your play style.

That being said, don't worry too much about having the best character possible
right away.  It's almost impossible to do unless you know both the game and the
d20 system very well.  You can still have an effective character though with
the right gear and the right feats and class combinations.

The beauty of the system is that there are so many combinations that it is almost
unheard of for two people to have the exact same build.  However that may change
as the game grows, as people will find out what works best, and 'cookie cutter'
builds may be made.  But even if that happens, we will ensure that even though
such builds may be popular, any intelligently done build will be effective, so
plan your character based on your own desires, and not based on what people
necessarily say is the best.

We are committed to game balance, so feel assured that if something gives an
unfair advantage, the system will be fixed to accommodate for that one way or
another.

If you ever have a question about d20 rules, a skill or a spell or a feat, or
some other concept that there's no help file for, please visit one of the 
following two web sites for the information you need.  Note that though we don't
always follow these web sites to the 'T', the information you gain should be
relevant enough to help you plan your build in 99% of the cases.

http://www.d20srd.com/
http://www.d20pfsrd.com/

As always, if you have any other question, please ask on chat, newbie or
submit a petition for a GM.

Thanks!

Gicker and the d20MUD Team

