FEATS

Usage: feats  <available | complete | known>

Feats can grant you a number of different things. Some feats allow you to wear
new armor, or wield new weapons. Some feats will give you bonus to skills you
already know, and other feats may grant you entirely new commands!

The feats command will allow you to see various information related to feats in
the game. Available shows you feats which are currently eligible to learn.
Complete shows all feats in the game. Known shows you feats you currently know.
You gain feats as you increase in level.

Without any argument it defaults to feats known. 

Not all feats are currently implemented.

All feats can be accessed by typing help feat <featname>.  If you do not see a help
file for a feat, it has not yet been done.  Please make a note of it with a forum
post or by using the bug command, and then refer to http://www.d20srd.org/ to find the
information you need on the specific feat.

See Also: LEARN, GAIN

