MEMORIZE STOP FORGET AUTOMEM

Usage: memorize <spell name>

The memorize command will allow you to manage your memorized spells, if you
are a spell caster. Without any argument it will display information regarding
The spell levels you can learn, the number of spell slots per spell level, any
spells that are currently memorized, and any spells you are still trying to
commit to memory. You can memorize spells without resting, however it takes
much longer. 

There are two kinds of spell casters in the game, Arcane and Divine. Arcane
spell casters need to have a spell book (or scroll) in their inventory with
the spell they wish to memorize. Divine spell casters need to have an item
of divine favor (holy symbol). Currently an item will qualify as an item
of divine favor if it has the ITEM_BLESS flag set on it.

To automatically reme your spells when you cast them type 'automem'

To forget a spell you have memorized type 'forget <spellname>'

To stop memorizing a spell you are currently memorizing type 'stop <spellname>'

See Also: SPELLS, MAGIC

