1 INTRODUCTION


First of all, welcome to our game.  This game has been an official work-in-progress
since Feburary of 2005, and before that has seen different incarnations, firstly
a d20 dragonlance MUD called Gates of Krynn, which was scrapped.  The code for that
MUD was donated to Zizazat of CWG (Circle with Goodies... http://cwg.lazuras.org) who
used parts of it to develop his d20 codebase, CWG Rasputin, which in turn we used again
as the base for this codebase in 2005.

The idea of this game is simple.  We wish to cater to a certain niche of MUD players out
there.  First, we obviously are trying to attract fans of the d20 System, D&&D 3.5e
and Pathfinder RPG.  Second, we wish to attract a certain type of player, or rather
avoid a certain type of player, that being the 'trouble maker'.

Essentially our goal is to provide our players with both an original and feature-
rich OGL rules game and a positive and friendly community in which they can feel
at home and relaxed within.  We have established rules, that, perhaps to some may
seem harsh, but which are done, not with the intention of policing our players, but
to weed out those who would have caused issues for our community to begin with, and
to develop a certain sub-culture within our community that generally revolves around
treating each other with respect, courtesy and kindness out of character.

If all of this sounds like something you can sink your teeth in, then by all means,
continue on with us.  We are very happy to have you with us :)  Because the game is
so unique, every player will experience a steep learning curve to some extent, however
we are confident that those who make it over the hump, will have found a game and
community like no other out there in the MUD world.

Thanks for joining.  Here's to many adventures and escapades together :)

