TICK PULSE
Ticks on Age of Dragons

A tick is a measure of time by which many things in this game are based
upon, including resting, memorizing spells, spell durations, and so on.

The time for one tick on Age of Dragons is approximately 90 seconds.

This equates to 1 hour in game time.  Thus 24 hours in game time would be
24 * 90 = 2160 secs / 60 seconds/minute = 36 minutes.

See Also: TIME, DATE













#0
BUGS

Bugs are a natural part of any game, especially one that has continued development.
However with bugs comes exploits and loopholes.  Since the mud is currently in beta
there will be even more exploits and loopholes.

It is your solemn responsability as a player to report bugs when you find them.  Do
not tell them to staff members.  Firstly, we will not always remember them.  Secondly
we are, at this stage of the game, here to work on and expand the mud, and the
fewer interruptions we have the better.  We are always happy to answer newbie related
questions, but appreciate it greatly when players take the initiative to be as
independant as possible, such as using the bug command to submit bugs (or the idea
command to submit ideas).  An immortal who is trying to work who gets interrupted
every 20 seconds is likely to get irritated, and may behave accordingly.

So what is a bug?  I don't think this needs definition to anyone who has played any
kind of video game over the years.  A bug is quite simply anything that enhances your
character without you having to do any real work to get it.  Be it experience,
gold, skill points, or anything that enhances your character, any bug that is used
more than once (the first time being the time you noticed it as a bug), will result
in the character being deleted and quite possibly banned.

We, as the staff, have been running these games for a long time and have heard every
excuse in the book, and frankly, we have to patience for them.  You are to do
*everything possible* to avoid repeating a bug.  And you must report it using the
bug command the moment you find it or suspect it of being a bug.  From there leave
it in the hands of a staff member, and check the news frequently to see if the bug has
been fixed.

We have much to do on this game, but our primary focus will be finding and fixing bugs
of already-existing features before adding new ones.  We appreciate your cooperation in
this matter.

--The Staff

Usage: bug <bug report>

This is the syntax for the bug command to report bugs.

Examples:
> bug the entire game crashes when I type 'put bag in bag'



The preferred method of reporting bugs is to report them on the
d20mud.com website wiki page at http://www.d20mud.com/wiki/

