Trip

The Trip Combat Ability:

   The trip combat ability is a combat ability usable by anyone during or before
combat.  Using this ability on someone will initiate combat if it is not
currently underway.  Only those in the first 3 fighting ranks can trip an
opponent.  

A simple trip check is performed as follows:

  Tripping attacker rolls an unarmed attack roll (dodge bonus only to ac, no armor).
If successful he rolls a second d20 trip roll to see if he can trip his opponent.
He adds his strength modifier and +4 for every size rank above medium, or -4 for every
rank below medium.

  The defender rolls a d20 trip defense roll and adds the greatest of his strength modifier
and his dexterity modifier.  If he is stable (ie. a dwarf or minotaur) or he has more than
two legs he add a bonus from +2 to +4.  He adds +4 for every size rank above medium and
-4 for every rank below medium.

  If the attacker's roll is greater than or equal to the defenders, the defender is tripped,
put on his feet, and stunned for one extra round.  If the defender wins the roll, he may attempt
to trip the attacker for free with one try.  If this check fails, nothing happens.

The attacker gets a number of trip attempts equal to his number of attacks, with the
appropriate attack bonus for each rank.  If he has the improved trip feat he receives one
extra trip attempt at maximum attack bonus.  Any unused attacks are not used that round, unless
the character is a monk.

Once tripped a character must use a movement action to stand up again, which will
drop his maximum number of attacks that round to 1.

