CLASS-ABILITIES-INSPIRE-COURAGE
Inspire Courage (Su)

A bard with 3 or more ranks in a Perform skill can use song or poetics to inspire courage in
his allies (including himself), bolstering them against fear and improving their combat 
abilities. To be affected, an ally must be able to hear the bard sing. The effect lasts for 
as long as the ally hears the bard sing and for 5 rounds thereafter. An affected ally 
receives a +1 morale bonus on saving throws against charm and fear effects and a +1 morale 
bonus on attack and weapon damage rolls. At 8th level, and every six bard levels thereafter, 
this bonus increases by 1 (+2 at 8th, +3 at 14th, and +4 at 20th). Inspire courage is a 
mind-affecting ability. 

