CLASS-BESERKER
Beserker

Alignment: Any Non-Lawful

Either born in the wilds or rejecting the comforttable life of the city life, beserkers are
confused by the complex rules of civilized society and are never truly comfortable behind 
walls. Beserkers are tough resilient survivors. They make fierce combatants and are both 
valued and feard for their prowess in battle.

Religion

Beserkers worship is usually casual, though tribal clerics and druids command respect. 
Beserkers revere the dieties of nature: Habbakuk, Chislev or Zeboim, depending on their
alignment.

Races

Most beserkers in Ansalon are human nomads, Kagonesti elves, or ogres. Almost all other 
races produce occassional beserkers with the exception of the gnomes of Mt. Nevermind. Even 
kender raised in wilder regions have been known to become fierce wilderness warriors.

**Taken from the Dragonlance Campaign setting, with the noted change of class Barbarian,
being named class Beserker to avoid confusion between races of barbarians (nomads) and the 
class.

*Class Skills (and the key ability for each skill)


Climb (Str)              Listen (Wis)
Craft (Int)              Ride (Dex)
Handle Animal (Cha)      Survival (Wis)
Intimidate (Cha)         Swim (Str) 
Jump (Str)

*Note: type help SKILL-<SKILL-NAME> for more information on indvidual skills.

CLASS FEATURES

Weapon and Armor Proficiency

A beserker is proficient with all simple and martial weapons, light armor, medium armor, and 
shields (except tower shields). 

Illiteracy

Beserkers are the only characters who do not automatically know how to read and write. A 
beserker may spend 2 skill points to gain the ability to read and write all languages he is
able to speak. 

A beserker who gains a level in any other class automatically gains literacy. Any other 
character who gains a beserker level does not lose the literacy he or she already had. 

*Beserker Class Abilities:

Fast Movement (Ex)                 Damage Reduction (Ex)
Rage (Ex)                          Greater Rage (Ex)
Uncanny Dodge (Ex)                 Indomitable Will (Ex)
Trap Sense (Ex)                    Tireless Rage (Ex)
Improved Uncanny Dodge (Ex)        Mighty Rage (Ex)

*Note: type help CLASS-ABILITIES-<ABILITY-NAME> for more information on individual abilites.

Ex-beserkers

A beserker who becomes lawful loses the ability to rage and cannot gain more levels as a 
beserker. He retains all the other benefits of the class (damage reduction, fast movement, 
trap sense, and uncanny dodge). 

SEE: http://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/barbarian.htm for more information on this class. Age
of Legends renamed the class from Barbarian to Beserker to avoid confusion with the race 
Barbarian (nomads, plainsmen). 

