CHARACTER-CREDITS

We have a credit system here on Age of Legends: Tales of the Lance.

What are credits?

Credits are a form of currency possessed by each character, that are gained by gaining 
levels, completing imm-run quests, good and frequent role playing, and in other ways as 
well.

Credits are used to purchase enhancements for your character. These enhancements can be 
extra experience, extra money, unique items, and other special perks.
Credits are obtained only through in-game achievements and cannot be bought with real 
money or through any other method.

Here is a quick list of what you can buy with credits:

-Steel coins (1000 steel coins per credit)
-Experience (1000 experience points per credit)
-Player House (10 credits)
-Extra room on your player house (8 credits)
-yourname@@ageofmortalsmud.com email address hosted by gmail (20 credits)
-Unique, reimbursable item, you must provide the descs and desired stats (1 credit per 2 
item levels, round up, min 5 credits)
-Non-reimbursable item restring, you must provide the descs (1 credit)
-Reimbursable item restring, you must provide the descs(3 credits)
-Title change, you must be eligable for the title... knights of neraka cannot have knights 
of solamnia titles (1 credit)
-Character descriptions reset (5 credits)
-Character respec (10 credits)
-Create new character with advanced race (depends on race, starts at 20 credits)

We welcome additional ideas for credit rewards, though the final say
on what they cost will be up to the administration.

If you wish to redeem your credits, please speak to an administrator or
head administrator.  Tools are coming soon so you can redeem your credits
yourself for certain items.

Some rewards can be gained automatically.  use the spendcredits command to view
and redeem these rewards with your credits.

