FEAT-WEAPONS-OF-CHOICE

Requirement: Weapon Master Level 1

The weapons of choice feat make it so that all of the weapons in
which you have the weapon focus feat in, are eligable for the various
weapon master bonuses.  There is no limit to how many different weapons
you may take with the weapon focus feat, and thus there is no limit to
how many weapons of choice you may have.

The feats associated with weapons of choice are:

Ki Damage
Increased Multiplier
Superior Weapon Focus
Ki Critical

See the help files on each of these feats for more information.  The
proper syntax is help feat <featname>

#0
FEAT-KI-DAMAGE

Requirement: Weapon Master Level 1

The Ki Damage feat gives the user an extra chance with each successful hit
to deal maximum weapon damage with their weapon, so long as they have
the weapon focus feat in that weapon, and have the weapons of choice
feat as well.

For each rank they have in ki damage, the chance to deal maximum damage
per weapon damage die roll increases by 5 percent with a base chance of 10 percent.
That gives 1 rank a chance of 15 percent and every rank over that an addition 5 percent.
This chance is rolled every time the weapon dice are rolled.  So for normal hits 
and once per critical multiplier for critical hits.
#0
FEAT-INCREASED-MULTIPLIER

Requirement: Weapon Master Level 3

The increased multiplier feat increases the critical damage multiplier of
your weapon by 1x.  So if your weapon is normally x2, this feat raises
it to x3, x3 to x4, and so on.  This effect is cumulative with all other
bonuses that increase the critical multiplier of weapons.

#0
FEAT-SUPERIOR-WEAPON-FOCUS

Requirement: Weapon Master Level 5

The superior weapon focus feat gives the wielder a +1 to hit rolls
whenever using a weapon that is considered a weapon of choice for
their wielder.

This bonus is cumulative with all other to hit bonuses.

#0
FEAT-KI-CRITICAL

Requirement: Weapon Master Level 7

The ki critical feat increases the threat range of a weapon to
determine critical hits by 1 for each rank in the feat.  This
increase only takes effect if the weapon is considered a weapon of
choice for the wielder.

It is cumulative with all other bonuses that increase the threat
range of weapons, including keen weapons, and the weapon of impact
spell.

