CRAFTING-SYSTEM

The crafting system is used to help supplement the equipment players
receive from killing mobs and doing quests.  Crafting can be a long
process, but the ability to get the exact equipment you want is one
of the greatest rewards for crafting, not to mention the potential
monetary gain involved.

Crafting generally takes place in two phases.  First is the harvesting
of resources.  For more information on harvesting resources type @Yhelp
harvesting@n.  The next step is crafting the item.  For more information
on crafting items type @Yhelp crafting items@n.

Crafting takes place using different skills.  Either a harvesting skill
to obtain the resources, or a crafting skill to make the item.

Harvesting Skills:
@WHerbalism@n: Used for gaining herbs for use in alchemy to make potions,
salves, and magical essences.
@WFarming@n: Used for gaining food resources for use in creating food and
drink buffs.
@WHunting@n: Hunting is used to find minor food in the wilderness,
the skinning of animals, and also the collection of lumber for
use in woodworking.
@WMining@n: Mining is used to gain metals and gemstones for use in
the blacksmithing and goldsmithing crafts.

Crafting Skills:
@WAlchemy@n: Used to create potions, salves and magical essences.
@WTailoring@n: Used to make magical and decorarative clothing as well
as bags.
@WWoodworking@n: Used to create wooden weapons, bows, arrows and other
missiles, and furniture for houses.
@WCooking@n: Used to make food and drink buffs.

@WTanning@N: Used to make leather and dragonhide armors.  Also boots, gloves
and belts.
@WGoldsmithing@n: Used to make rings, necklaces, bracers and other jewelry and
trinkets.
@WBlacksmithing@N: Used to make metal weapons and armors.

The commands linked with each craft or harvesting skill are as
follows:

forge --> blacksmithing, weave --> tailoring, brew --> alchemy, 
cook --> cooking, assemble --> woodworking, tan --> tanning,
craft --> goldsmithing, forge --> blacksmithing, gather --> herbalism,
harvest --> farming, hunt --> hunting, mine --> mining.


@nYou may also create items using the custom crafting system, please see
@Yhelp custom crafting system@n for more information.
#0
HARVESTING

Harvesting is the means of gathering resources for the purpose
of crafting items.  In order to successfully harvest something you
must be in a room that provides the resources.  For example, if you
want to mine ore, you must go to a mountain or cave where there is
ore to mine.  It is up to you to find which rooms these are.

You begin harvesting by typing the harvesting command.  Then, after
a certain amount of time, generally 2 minutes for most classes and
less for higher level artisans, you will either succeed or fail
depending on your skill in that type of harvesting, and the richness
of the resource deposit in the room.

Each room can be harvested a maximum of 5 times per 20 minute cycle,
after which the room resets and can be harvested another 5 times.
#0
CRAFTING-ITEMS

  Crafting items is done once you have the resources needed to
create the item.  You can see what items you can craft by typing
your craft command and list.  So to see what items I can forge I
would type forge list.  You can see what components each item needs
by typing listcomponents and the item description.  So if I wanted
to see what items I need to craft a steel kukri, I would type
listcomponents a steel kukri.

In general they higher the level of your crafting skill, the more
powerful items you can create.

