RULES-NAMES

@RORIGINAL FANTASY-BASED NAMES ONLY PLEASE@n

1) No modern names.  If a name wasn't in popular use in medieval times
then it is not acceptable.  For example Alexander would be acceptable
whereas Betsy would not be.

No names from existing fictional works.  That includes Dragonlance
characters.  Do not use names from novels, movies, comics, or what have you.
Please be original with your names.

3) No modern day nouns as names.  It's ok to call your character something
like Scimitar or Knife, because these are possible nicknames people from
the underworld might call themselves or each other.  However in such circumstances
it is expected for you to invent a real name for your character following
these guidelines for role playing purposes.  It would not be acceptable to
call your character Bazooka or Bomber because Bazookas and Bombs don't
exist in a medieval setting.

4) No compound names.  Depending on your race, please do not use compound
names, such as madkiller.  Something like firestar might be acceptable for
a wild elf or a barbarian, because both fire and star are common things in
a medieval fantasy world.  It is thinkable that someone from these cultures
might name their child this.  Madkiller on the other hand is something
no one would name their child, and is unlikely someone would name themselves
either.

In general we ask that you simply make an attempt to use a name that is
original and that make sense in a fantasy medieval world.  If you create
a character with an invalid name you will be asked to change it.  If you
comply with cooperation we will reimburse your character's gear and
levels.  Otherwise we will be forced to unfortunately, delete you.

If you need help choosing a name consider using this name generator:
@Whttp://www.seventhsanctum.com/index-name.php@n

Thanks for your cooperation in this matter.  It will help enhance the
role play of the game and the fun for all involved.
