CUSTOM-CRAFTING-SYSTEM

  The custom crafting system works a little differently than the recipe-based
crafting system.  You are able to create any item at all without having to
refer to a specific recipe.

First you need a crafting station.  They are available in all of the major
cities.  You will need a stock mold item, which can be bought from the mundane
item shops, and you will need enough materials to match the weight of the item
you wish to create, and finally if you wish the item to be magical you will
need magical essences of some type.

To begin put your mold item, your materials and your essences in the crafting
station.  For every 4 essences of the same type you put in the station, the
bonus will increase by +1 (or more depending on the bonus type).  Once you
have your items in the station, you need to use the create command to create
your item.

Type create <item description> to create the item.  The item description is
very important.  You can use color in your item descriptions, but it must
contain the material type and the item type name in the description.  It also
must coincide with the forgotten realms world and be a physical description.

Good Desc:
a shimmering steel long sword with a gem-studded hilt

Bad Descs:
a steel long sword of death
the steel long sword of killing Elvis

We immortals retain the right to take away any item we feel interferes with
the role playing environment without reimbursing the item or materials used
to craft it, so please use good sense when creating your item descriptions.

Once you type create <description> you will begin the crafting process,
assuming your skill is high enough.  After about 2 minutes, you will make
a skill roll.  The more powerful the item the more difficult the dc.  If you
fail you lose the item and all materials.  If you succeed you gain the item
you were crafting.


A couple of final notes:
- The essence must go into the crafting system after everything else
- You can only use one material in your items, though your desc can contain more
- Currently only one essence type will take effect.  If you put in two different
essences in your recipe, only the last one put in will be used.  Essences of
the same type and power are fine, other essences will be lost.
- Don't forget you can mine metals with the mining skill and disenchant magic
items for essences with the spellcraft skill.
