CLASS-DUELIST

The duelist is one who specializes in one-on-one combat.  They excel so much at
this that they are almost unmatched when fighting one on one.  They use light
fencing weapons usually and wear little or no armor.  They are often flashy
and extroverted individuals who travel from place to place ever seeking greater
challenges to their swordplay.

Requirements: +6 base attack bonus, 3 ranks in perform, 5 ranks in tumble, 
 dodge, mobility, weapon finesse
Hit Die: 1d10
High Saves: Reflex
Base Attack: +1 per level
Level Up Command: gain duelist
Important Stats: Dexterity for hit chance and potential damage bonus with
 improved weapon finesse, as well as ac, Int for skills and ac bonus, Con for
 additional hit points.
Skill Points Per Level: 4 + Int Modifier
Class Skills: Balance, Bluff, Escape Artist, Jump, Listen, Perform, Sense
 Motive, Spot, Tumble
Class Abilities: Canny Defense (1), Improved Reaction (2, 8), Enhanced 
 Mobility (3), Grace (4), Precise Strike (5, 10), Acrobatic Charge (6),
 Elaborate Parry (7), Deflect Arrows (9).
Notes: A duelist adds his duelist level to his combat tactics skill for the
 purpose of determining parry attempts.  He may only attempt to parry the
 attacks of his main opponent, and not subsequent foes he may be fighting.

