spell-charm-animal
This charm makes a animal creature regard you as its trusted friend and 
ally (treat the targets attitude as friendly). If the creature is currently
being threatened or attacked by you or your allies, however, it receives a +5
bonus on its saving throw.
@n
The spell does not enable you to control the charmed animal as if it were an
automaton, but it perceives your words and actions in the most favorable way.
You can try to give the subject orders, but you must win an opposed Charisma 
check to convince it to do anything it wouldnt ordinarily do. (Retries are not
allowed.) An affected creature never obeys suicidal or obviously harmful orders,
but it might be convinced that something very dangerous is worth doing. Any act 
by you or your apparent allies that threatens the charmed person breaks the spell.
@n
