CLASS-MAGE

 @nThe mage's strength is her spells.  Everything else is secondary. She learns
 new spells as she experiments and grows in experience, and she can also learn
 them from other mages. In addition to learning new spells, a mage can, over
 time, learn to manipulate her spells so they go farther, work better, or are
 improved in some other way.

 Overall, mages show a slight tendency toward law over chaos because the study
 of magic rewards those who are disciplined. Illusionists and transmuters,
 however, are masters of deception and change, respectively.  They favor chaos
 over law.

@YMage Class Features@n
 Alignment:       Any
 Hit Die:         d4
 Primary Stat:    Intelligence (Spell Casting)
 Secondary Stats: Dexterity (Armor) and Constitution (Hit Points)

@YSpells@n
 A mage casts arcane spells which are drawn from the sorcerer/mage spell list.

 A mage must choose and prepare her spells ahead of time using the @Ymem@n command.
 Ex: mem light
     mem magic-missile

 To learn, prepare, or cast a spell, the mage must have an Intelligence score equal
 to at least 10 + the spell level. The Difficulty Class for a saving throw against a
 mages spell is 10 + the spell level + the mage's Intelligence modifier.

 Mages cast spells using the @Ycast@n command.
 Ex: cast 'magic missile' <target>

@YClass Skills@n
 Concentration (Con), Craft (Int), Decipher Script (Int), Profession (Wis),
 Spellcraft (Int).

 Skill Points at 1st Level: (2 + Int modifier) x 4
 Skill Points at Each Level: 2 + Int modifier

@YWeapon and Armor Proficieny@n
 Proficient with the club, dagger, heavy crossbow, light crossbow, and
 quarterstaff, but not with any type of armor or shield. Armor of any type
 interferes with a mage's movements, which can cause her spells with
 somatic components to fail.

 For a table explaining Wizard level gains, type @Yhelp table wizard@n.
 For a spell table for wizards, type @Yhelp spelltable wizard@n.
 For a spell listing for wizards, type @Yhelp spelllist wizard@n.
 For a list of wizard bonus feats, type @Yhelp bonus feats wizard@n.

