CLASS-ABILITY-KI-DAMAGE
@n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@n
&YAs a Weapon Master
@n After you score a hit with your weaponof choice, you do not roll dice to
@n determine the damage.  Instead, you figure the normal maximum damage (not a
@n critical hit) you can inflict with that weapon and do that much damage to the
@n target. Assume you use a longsword, have a base attack bonus of +7, and 
@n possess a 17 Strength. A longsword does 1d8 damage, so its maximum damage is
@n 8 points. Your strength modifier is +3, so add that for a total of 11.
@n Additional damage, such as from using the Power Attack feat and the sneak
@n attack ability are determined normally, they are not maximized. This ability
@n cannot be used when you roll a successful critical hit.
@n
@n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------@n
#0
CLASS-ABILITY-INCREASED-MULTIPLIER
@n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@n
&YAs a Weapon Master
@n Determine the standard critical multiplier for your weapon of choice. With this
@n ability, you can increase that multiplier by +1. For example, the longsword has
@n a critical mutliplier of X2. Using this ability, you can increase that to X3
@n once per day at 2nd level. You must declare the use of this ability before you
@n roll any damage dice.
@n
@n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------@n
