RULES-TITLES

@RFANTASY BASED TITLES ONLY.  NO STATUS UPDATES PLEASE@n

You may set your own title using the title command but we have certain rules
that go along with this feature and allowance.  The main idea is that all
titles must be in character and appropriate for your character in some way.

We don't want to see frivilous titles or titles that advertise your current
mood or character's state of being.  A title is just that, a title, it
is not meant to be an expression of philosophy, mood, humor, or anything
else.  Also your title must include your character's name.

Here are some examples of good titles:
Caide Delancis, Purple Dragon Knight of Cormyr
Thoran Khadgar, Chieftain's Son of the Tribe of the Bear
Valos D'Raden, Initiate of the Hosttower of the Arcane

Here are some bad examples of titles:
Caide is tired of all the snow.
Thoran is feeling super awesome!
Valos - Owner of all Halflings in Faerun

These rules are very clear, and if they are not, ask an imm before you set
your title.  If you set your title to something inappropriate, it will be
changed for you.  If you do this more than once, you will lose the ability
to set your own title until we feel we can trust you with it again, which
may take months.


It should also be noted that a title does not have to be legitimate.  For
example, one could set their title to attempt to pose as something else, such
as a Knight of Solamnia, or a Lord, or what have you.  The only thing that is not
allowed here is attempting to impersonate a specific person.  In such cases
disciplinary action will be taken.

