REMAKE-RULES
Remaking your character is not something that you can do just because
you have decided you don't like where you put your stats or how you
chose your feats. There are only two ways to have your character
remade. The first way is to have 20,000 account experience accrued.
The same rules for previous remakes applies, except you can change
your classes as long as the general character idea stays the same.
Generally your basic classes should remain more or less the same,
and prestige classes should change. A mage could change to a sorcerer,
but not to a cleric or a fighter.

The second way is if your character is bugged and the only way to
fix it is to remake your character to get rid of the bug.


If you feel you are bugged please let the staff know and we will
be in touch with you about the problem. If you wish to remake
useing your account experience you must first submit a request
to the staff about why you wish to remake. We will then review it
and speak with you about it.
