LFG

  The lfg command is used for looking for groups.  The syntax is as follows:

lfg:
  This will list all players on the mud current looking for a group.

lfg set:
  This will toggle whether you are looking for a group or not.  Once
  you are grouped your lfg flag will automatically be removed.

lfg <string>:
  This will set your lfg string to tell people what you are looking
  for.  This can be a maximum of 60 characters included color characters.

See Also: @YLFG@n, @YGROUP@n

