ROLE-PLAYING

Role playing is encouraged here on d20mud: Forgotten Realms, though it is
not enforced.

A lot of information is available on this mud, not all of which is known
by your character.  Anything labelled IC (in character) is able to be known
by your character.  Everything else is OOC (out of character) and is known
only by you, the player, and it is expected that you make an effort to separate
what you know from what your character knows, also known as meta-gaming.

IC Information includes: anything said with the say command, anything seen
with the look command, all objects, rooms and mobs are ic, unless otherwise
stated in their descriptions, combat is considered ic, so be careful what
you kill in whose presence, and be extra careful about killing citizens of
cities while others are around, information shown by your score is ic,
introductions are ic, narrate channel is ic.

Everything else is ooc, and is not known by your character.  When it comes
to things like stats your character only knows general effectiveness.  He
does not know a longsword is +4, but he does know it has a powerful
enchantment on it if he has identified it somehow.  The same goes for character
stats, skills, feats, abilities and so on.  Exact numbers are not known by
characters, but general effects and extent thereof is.

If you have any questions about what else is considered ic or ooc, please
ask an imm or another player.  If you cannot get your answer on chat or newbie,
consider making a post on our forums.

