5 MOVEMENT
@nThis MUD uses rooms which are linked together. Rooms are a generalization for
underground sewer, or a fairly large path in the forest. The best way to think
about rooms, is that they are all points on a map with specific exits.
@n
Exits include "@Cnorth@n" "@Ceast@n" "@Csouth@n" "@Cwest@n" "@Cup@n" "@Cdown@n" "@Cnorthwest@n" "@Cnortheast@n"
@Csouthwest@n and "@Csoutheast@n"
@n
At any time, you can type "look" and see your current room. Available exits
will be displayed underneath the "Obvious Exits" field, and also in the minimap
on the right side of the displayed text. Typing "exits" will display just the
available exits in your current room.
@n
To move around, simple type the direction you want to go. For example, type "n"
to go north. Sometimes, you may encounter a barrier in your way, such as a door
or gate. When you walk into one of these, you'll receive a message similar to
The cell seems to be closed.
In this message, "cell" is the name of the door, so we can "open cell" to open
this pathway. Sometimes, you will also see the following.
It seems to be locked.
This means that the exit is locked. A person with a high "open lock" skill can
try to "pick cell" to pick open the lock, or simply having the key in your
inventory and typing "unlock cell" will unlock the door.
@n
As far as the automap goes, if you type in "map" you will see a larger version
of the automap, as well as a key displaying the room types.
@n
If you ever with to turn the automap function off, simply type "@Cautomap@n" to
toggle it on and off.
