ABOUT-THE-GAME ABOUT-d20MUD


d20MUD is essentially an OGL Rules Multi User Dungeon.  While our original rule
set was the d20 System, quite a bit has been released since then, especially
with the Pathfinder RPG System, that we have decided to switch from d20 to OGL
instead.

Generally what you can expect from us is to use either d20 rules or Pathfinder
RPG rules whereever possible in-game.  At times we may deviate from these rules
when the stock OGL systems in place are not friendly for or balanced towards a
persistant world type of game.  An example of this is crafting.  In such cases we
will generally look outwards to the rest of the MUD and MMORPG world to find
examples of systems which we think both work well from a balance standpoint and
are also fun to use.

This game is also ever changing.  I expect we will become quite (in)famous for
using the NERF bat.  In essence, we want to create a game that evolves with our
players.  That being said, we know the damage that can be done to games and
communities when the core essence of that game is dramatically altered (Star Wars
Galaxies anyone?), so we will be very careful to keep our alterations minor in
effect wherever possible, and we will also try to make attempts to appease the
majority of our player base.  We will also make as many attempts as possible to
add new features instead of change existing ones.  However despite our best
intentions and efforts, from time to time, a feature we present to the game simply
may not work well, either because functionally it is hard to learn or use, or
because it simply presents game balance issues that severely effect the
game's economy or progression scale.  In such situations we will make the corrections
we feel are necessary, but will always attempt to find out what our player
base thinks are solutions before deciding on a final implementation.

With that said, you can learn more about our game by reading @YHELP INTRODUCTION@n
but to sum things up, our game is meant to give people who like OGL style rules and
who generally enjoy getting along with others, a home here on the Internet where they
can satisfy both desires.

At any time if you have a suggestion or question that can't be answered by another
player, staff member or help file, please contact the owner, Steve Squires at
stephen.squires@@gmail.com.  While he won't necessarily always be the person running
the game, he will always make sure that it maintains the principles upon which it was
built, and is always available to help people understand the game better.

