RESIZE

You may resize any weapon, armor or shield to be larger or smaller.  Large
races may need to resize some armor to fit them, and weapons can be resized to
alter both their damage and their eligibility for certain feats such as weapon
finesse and monkey grip.

You need a crafting station to resize something.  You must put the original item
in the station along with enough of the same material the item is made of to 
compensate for the new size and then type resize followed by the new size.

So say I want to resize a steel longsword +1.  I would put the sword in the station
and then I would put in enough steel to compensate for the new size I want, which
in this case is large, and then I type 'resize large'.  The resizing process would
then begin and a few short moments later, the newly resized longsword +1 would appear
in my inventory.

