RACE-ICE-FOLK
The Ice Folk are the Humans that live in the frozen reaches of the Panak Desert. 
They are split into various clans and tribes, but are commonly all united 
as Ice Folk. They do not fight amongst the tribes and clans, but are united 
against the elements and outsiders.

The Ice Folk are generally tall and well built, with a thick layer of fat over 
their bodies to keep them warm in the frigid conditions. They have flattened faces, 
tiny eyes and pug shaped noses, and ears with small lobes. Most Ice Folk have black 
hair, and the males generally all grow short black beards. The clothing of the Ice 
Folk is all made from furs and hides, chiefly of nasif wool, and pants of seal-skin. 
The primary weapon of the Ice Folk are spears, since they are mainly hunters and not 
warlike, although they also rely on axes.

They were once ruled by shamans who wielded divine magic, but with the loss of the 
gods following the Great Destruction, the panicked Ice Folk turned on the shamans, 
blaming them for the loss of the gods. 
The shamans were driven out or killed, and the makau, who wielded arcane magic, 
stepped in to fill the void. The makau, who were once just advisors, became 
the leaders of the clans in the aftermath, and lead most of the existing clans today.
