PLAYER-SHOPS

  Players can purchase their own shop for 20,000 steel coins.  This shop functions
much like a house, except for some subtle differences.  If you wish to purchase a
player shop please speak with either Gicker or Dran.

Only the shop owner and people on the guest list (see house command) are able
to drop and get items out of the room, as well as place sale values on items in
their inventory.

The commands when in a shop are as follows:

shop buy <item keywords>
shop sell <item keywords> <sell value>
shop try <item keywords>

The try command will allow you to identify an item.  Please note that it is against
the rules to set an item's description to something aside from what it actually is using
the restring command.  Attempts to deceive and cheat people out of their money is not
allowed here, and those who attempt to do so will be dealt with harshly, no matter what
your character's alignment or personality is in character.

We recommend you always try an item before buying it, and to ensure you are targetting the
proper item with your keywords using the try command before buying.

The sell command allows someone to place a sell value on an item in their inventory, which can
then be dropped in the room to be sold.  Remember to type save after dropping an item in your
shop/house.

The buy command will transfer the item to your inventory, remove the sale price, and leave a pile
of gold coins for the sale on the floor of the room, which only the shop owner or those
on the guest list are able to pick up.

See Also: SHOPS, HOUSES

