CLASS-FAVORED-SOUL

The favored soul is a chosen champion of his god or goddess.  Unlike
clerics however, they do not choose their life but rather instead they
are chosen of the gods to be their emissary, often from childhood.  Though
some favored souls are similar to paladins in ideals and behavior, they
can be of any alignment, and serve any diety.
 
A favored soul focuses on the deity's favored weapon and gains proficiency
often on par with a fighter in it as they level up.  
 
@YFavored Soul Class Features@n
 Alignment:    Any (Same as deity, or one step removed)
 Hit Die:      d8
 Primary Stat: Charisma (Spell dc based on Wisdom)
 
@YSpells@n
 A favored soul casts divine spells, which are drawn from the cleric spell list. However,
 his alignment may restrict him from casting certain spells opposed to his moral or
 ethical beliefs.
 
 A favored soul casts his spells spontaneously which are reset 10 minutes after the
 first one was cast.  There is no way to reduce this timer.
 
 A favored soul casts spells using the imbue command.
 Ex: imbue <spell> <target>
 
 To prepare or cast a spell, a favored soul must have a Charisma score equal to at least
 10 + the spell level. The Difficulty Class for a saving throw against a favored
 spell is 10 + the spell level + the favored soul's Wisdom modifier. 
 
@YClass Skills@n
 Concentration (Con), Diplomacy (Cha), Heal (Wis), Lore (Int), Spellcraft (Int).
 
@YWeapon and Armor Proficiency@n
 All simple weapons, deity's favored weapon, light and medium armor, and
 shields (except tower shields). Each deity has a favored weapon, and
 his or her favored souls consider it a point of pride to wield that weapon.
  
For a table explaining Favored Soul level gains, type @Yclassabilities favored soul.@n
For a spell table for favored souls, type @Yhelp spelltable favored soul.@n
For a spell listing for favored souls, type @Yhelp spelllist favored soul.@n
To cast a favored soul spell, type @Yimbue.@n
