OUTPUT

The output command allows you to alter the amount and length of messages you 
receive for various aspects of the game.
 
All output options have three settings: full, normal and sparse.
 
Normal setting is what everything is set to by default.  You don't have
to change anything to achieve this level, unless you have previously changed
to another value.
-
Full setting offers the most descriptive (and in some cases spammy) output for
the specified setting.
 
Sparse will minimize the output offered to as little as possible while still
maintaining the integrity of the message's information.
 
The current output possibilities are:
combat
 
Example usage: output combat full
 (Will set your combat output to full)
